<text id="A7157T">
<front id="d2">
<div1 type="summary" id="d3">
<p>Letter confirming receipt of vouchers</p> 
</div1> 

</front> 

<body id="d4">
<div1 type="letter" id="d5">
<head>
<name type="recipient">W. E. Whiting Esq</name> 
<name type="place">Staunton Va</name> 
</head>

<opener>
<dateline>
    <date value="1869-04-27">Apr 27<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1869</date> 
</dateline> 
<salute>Dear Sir</salute> 
</opener> 

<p>I have just read from the disbursing officer--(Maj Geo Q White B R F  H L) Richmond Va.--vouchers to be signed preparatory to the pay't of the $17.00 rent for month of Apr</p>
	<p>If the money is rec'd it will appear on the credit side of my monthly acct with you, at the close of the present month,--for which acct please send blanks by return mail.</p>


<closer>
<salute></salute> 
<signed>John Scott</signed> 

<name type="place">N Y</name> 
</closer> 
</div1> 
</body> 
</text> 
